The course will provide essential knowledge required for creating popular video games, includin: game design, graphics management,  psycholgoy, marketing and project management. The learner is expected to create a full game design document and, cooperating with others, a game (demo).Objectives/eesmärkid:  Provide the learner a structured knowledge of developing videogames and the steps required to do this, including game design, game psychology and marketing, with the general goal of teaching learners how to make successful videogames.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The learner who has completed the course knows all main elements of developing video games (including gaming psychology, game analysis and marketing), skills to create practical game design documents from ideas and start projects to make them real. The learner is expected to create a complete design document and also (collaborating with a team formed with other learners) a computer game (demo).The learners will receive help from the university and lector for organizing the developing teams, finding partners and marketing their games after completing the course.
